    "title": "The Red Cross1",
    "content": "Signs of an Emergency\n•Screaming, moaning, shouting, or calls for help\n•Sudden loud noises such as breaking glass, clashing metal,\nor screeching tires\n•A change in the sound made by machinery or equipment\n•An unusual silence\n•A stopped vehicle on the roadside or a car that has run offof the road\n•Downed electrical wires\n•Sparks, smoke, or fire\n•A person who suddenly collapses or is lying motionless\n•Signs or symptoms of illness or injury, such as profusesweating for no apparent reason or an uncharacteristic\nskin colour•A foul or unusually strong chemical odour\n•The smell of smoke\n•The smell of gas\n•An unrecognizable odour\n•An inappropriate odour (e.g., a sickly-sweet odour on aperson’s breath)\n•Confusion in a person who is normally alert\n•Unusual drowsiness\n•Personality or mood changes (e.g., agitation in aperson who is normally calm)UNUSUAL SOUNDS\nUNUSUAL SIGHTSUNUSUAL ODOURS\nUNUSUAL BEHAVIOURS\nResponding to Emergencies",
